cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

This paper focuses on the use of social media by news organizations to engage with their audience, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of algorithms to measure trustworthiness and audience engagement, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The paper also mentions the use of Twitter data, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between news organizations and their audience, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
